The Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS) has threatened to deduct the tax liabilities from bank accounts of defaulters In a statement credited to the Director of Communication, Mr Abdullahi Ahmad on Wednesday in Abuja, said that the action was being considered, “following rising cases of willful and illegal withholding of taxes collected by companies, corporations, Ministries, Departments, and Agencies (MDAs) and other agents of collection.”  In the statement Ahmad further, indicated that the agency would take steps “to recover taxes due from the defaulters’ asset in the custody of any person, including but not limited to sums standing to its credit with a financial institution in Nigeria”.  According to the source Nigerian-American Chamber of Commerce, the FIRS has sent notices to that effect have been served to all companies, corporate entities, and other agents of collection.  He stated that they were required to pay all outstanding tax liabilities to the FIRS within 30 days from the date of publication of the notice. 